Date:9/6/2010 4:28:34 PM
From:Spekulatius
re MRO
>> That's why I hate integrateds.<< it depends on what you pay for the R&M
part.
MRO's market cap is 28B%, proved reserves are 1.7BOE (60% oil / 40% gas).

The crude reserves are worth: 1.7x0.6x15$=15.3B$
gas reserves: 1.6x0.4x6x1.5$=5.76B$

So the reserves along cover 21B$ of MRO's 28B$ EV. For the rest you get a R&M
business that is able to generate 1B$ in profit in decent year, an integrated
gas business (worth probably 2B$+)plus an oils sand business (no proved
reserves were booked in the oils sand segment) plus ancillary assets.

This is pretty cheap in my book. I'll take a Refining and marketing asset ,
especially a best in class one any time if I don't have to pay for it.
